820
01:02:03,625 --> 01:02:08,556
[SPEAKER_14]: And the nurse wept as she said, we have to literally pay to bin these drugs.

821
01:02:08,596 --> 01:02:09,979
[SPEAKER_14]: We can't reuse them in this country.

822
01:02:10,280 --> 01:02:12,385
[SPEAKER_14]: We can't give them to third world countries.

823
01:02:12,405 --> 01:02:14,209
[SPEAKER_14]: That is a lack of common sense.

824
01:02:14,330 --> 01:02:14,791
[SPEAKER_14]: Well, let's get better.

825
01:02:14,811 --> 01:02:15,673
[SPEAKER_14]: We need to manage it better.

826
01:02:15,873 --> 01:02:16,254
[SPEAKER_14]: Understood.

827
01:02:16,274 --> 01:02:17,196
[SPEAKER_14]: Cut out the waste.

828
01:02:17,216 --> 01:02:19,281
[SPEAKER_14]: And we need to stop the drugs.

829
01:02:19,261 --> 01:02:25,830
[SPEAKER_14]: But what we do need to do is we need to stop the drugs companies from ripping off the NHS.

830
01:02:25,850 --> 01:02:32,960
[SPEAKER_04]: So just to be clear on the point about for sale, what the documents appear to say... Go on then, Rebecca Long-Bailey, you put the question to him.

831
01:02:33,000 --> 01:02:34,622
[SPEAKER_04]: Let Rebecca Long-Bailey put the question.

832
01:02:34,682 --> 01:02:36,204
[SPEAKER_04]: Let her put the question.

833
01:02:36,485 --> 01:02:37,506
