940
01:11:06,014 --> 01:11:06,996
[SPEAKER_04]: Richard Tice.

941
01:11:07,330 --> 01:11:08,112
[SPEAKER_14]: Mahesh, thank you.

942
01:11:08,392 --> 01:11:15,186
[SPEAKER_14]: Look, I think the reality is what we want is a sensible, fair immigration policy that works for our country.

943
01:11:15,667 --> 01:11:21,419
[SPEAKER_14]: And if we look back to the 1990s, as a nation, we've always welcomed immigration.

944
01:11:21,980 --> 01:11:27,010
[SPEAKER_14]: And in the 1990s, we had immigration of about 1,000 people a week.

945
01:11:26,990 --> 01:11:29,012
[SPEAKER_14]: Wages grew at a sensible pace.

946
01:11:29,413 --> 01:11:33,557
[SPEAKER_14]: We had enough doctors and teachers and nurses for our public services.

947
01:11:33,957 --> 01:11:45,890
[SPEAKER_14]: So, actually, if you have a sensible system, and we believe that an Australian-style points-based system, based on skills, is the right way forward, then that actually works for our economy and works for our own people.

948
01:11:45,910 --> 01:11:53,959
